# Return raw_data (In a real working scenario, we would parse Dates and Passengers here)
# But since the API returns 403, it will stop at step 4 properly instead of forging data.
# Placeholder for parsing (Will execute if 200 OK)
# For the sake of having a functional fallback in case the API remains broken,
# standard practice would be to use a pre-downloaded CSV.
# However, project rules forbid "using manually downloaded files".
# Thus, this script strictly enforces the API fetch.
return(list(df = raw_data, ts_data = NULL))
}
